{{Infobox language family |name=Fur |altname=For |region=[[Darfur]] and [[Chad]] |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |child1=[[Fur language|Fur]] |child2=[[Amdang language|Amdang]] |glotto=fura1235 |glottorefname=Furan }}
The '''Fur''' or '''For languages''' constitute a small, closely related family which are a proposed member of the [[Nilo-Saharan languages|Nilo-Saharan]] family. [[Fur language|Fur]] in western [[Sudan]] had around 750,000 speakers in 2004, and [[Amdang language|Amdang]] (also called [[Mimi language|Mimi]]) in eastern [[Chad]] had around 40,000 speakers in 2000.
