{{refimprove|date=December 2017}}
In broadcasting, a '''trimulcast''' is a cluster of three radio stations and/or translators that play the same feed. Normally this is done in order to have full coverage of a certain area. Some stations use this technique to provide [[Rimshot (broadcasting)|rimshot]] coverage into a major [[Media market|market]] by broadcasting on the outskirts from three different locations, or combine multiple [[low power television]] stations in an attempt to provide the equivalent coverage of one full-power station.
== Examples== *[[WGVX]]/WRXP/WWWM in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]] making up a [[classic hip hop]] station called '''105 The Vibe'''. *[[KRXV|KRXV, KHWY, and KHYZ]] cover the [[Mojave Desert]] from [[Barstow, California|Barstow]] to [[Laughlin, Nevada|Laughlin]] and [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], with its target audience being listeners travelling into Nevada on [[Interstate 15 (California)|Interstate 15]] and [[Interstate 40 (California)|Interstate 40]] from [[Southern California]]. *[[KBPI]]/[[KBPL]]/K300CP on 107.9 frequency cover the [[Interstate 25 in Colorado|Colorado Interstate 25 corridor]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://radioinsight.com/headlines/121387/iheart-begins-three-market-format-shuffle-cheyenne/|title=KBPI Moves To 107.9 As Three Station Trimulcast In Denver, Fort Collins & Colorado Springs|date=2017-12-11|work=RadioInsight|access-date=2017-12-21|language=en-US}}</ref>
